"I finally got this one finished. A lot of work and a lot of detail, so it may run a bit slow. I was paid to do it by some people who owned an internet cafe, and they were pretty picky on the details. They want to do tournaments on it. It is a map of a real place. It's big with all it's custom textures. Their is no objective, just kill the other team. CTs start in the front of the Internet Cafe, and the Ts start in the back. It's been play tested and is very balanced on sides.

Don't be afraid to use night vision, this map was built for it."

CS_PIPELINE by FragNaT1c (released October 2009)

The author of this winter atmospheric assault-themed map managed to create open space with the wide view on which would be possible various styles of military actions: from the sniping hunts to the closed combats. We appear in the snow-covered territory with complex of office buildings located lengthways a site of the Arctic oil pipeline. There are, of course, a lot of shot by snipers areas, but CTs certainly can bring hostages, avoiding open spaces, making the way through a underground tunnels and corridors, taking cover behind buildings and details of the landscape.

In spite of the fact that at creation of the map was used only standard materials (models, textures), it looks quite atmospheric and realistic (more or less). Anyway, battles proceed here very hazardously (imho).

A necessary attributes for comfortable gameplay (mini-map on radar, nav-file for bots) are embedded in the bsp-file. Unfortunately, the nav-file is simple auto-gen (not optimized manually), though it's more or less playable.

Well... Great Thanks to FragNaT1c for his Nice Work!
Pingo Tinto Portugal

**--cs_pilko_estate--**

**---A hostage rescue map by J4CK8 and Mikeypilk---**

Pilkington Estate is a hostage map based around a German, or Italian (but german police came to the rescue) mansion. The terrorists have taken over the building and are holding the hostages...well...hostage. Counter terrorists must search the building to find the 5 hostages located in and around the mansion and return them to safety. The map consists of 2 floors and a basement.

The map was created by me with help and ideas from Mikeypilk. It uses various custom textures take from the "Textures for the Real world" pack by TopHATTwaffle (http://www.gamebanana.com/members/144386) and some textures created by myself and Mikeypilk

The map includes:
-18 Spawn points per team
-Buyzones for both teams
-5 Hostages
-Custom materials
-Custom radar (Works but is limited*)
-Working nav file
-3d skybox

*As the map features 2 floors, the radar cannot display both floors and therefore will only display the top floor.

This is a new version of previously named cs_mansion. This updated version includes some more details here and there, a new basement entrance from ct spawn and new textures on the building. Some other bugs and fixes also included.


To install, extract the .BSP files to your cstrike/maps folder.

NOTE: SO SORRY ABOUT MISSING TEXTURE - FIXED!!! I fogot a func_illusionary was using a texture I made for another map months ago. Texture has now been included - please download cs_olympic again and overwrite the previous version (posted yesterday the 01/10/2010) if you would like to see the texture. Sorry again (i counted this morning - over 350 custom files in this map! - Im suprised I forgot only one :/ 

Hello Again. Well here it is, finally, the finished version of cs_olympic. Firstly, to anyone who downloaded and liked the beta version; I apolagize for the fact that it has taken so long to get out this finished version... I have a seasonal job which means from march to september I dont have the time for... well, anything really.

So the map... I am pleased with it, I think it is a big improvement over the beta version. Although the changes I have made are not dramatic, I think that they really make the difference and give the map the polished/complete feeling that the beta version lacked. Structurally almost nothing has changed, with the exception of some adjustments made to doorways to allow for better hostage movement. 

The changes since the beta version are far more concerned with lighting, models and textures. The beta version was an LDR map, the final version is HDR which by itself makes the map look much better. I have spent a lot of time trying to get the lighting right inside the building... Putting in a light entity is one of the easist things to do in hammer, but I think that creating a good lighting scheme in a map is probably one of  the hardest.

Using I have taken the opportunity to make some custom models for the map which look nice. I always had the intention of putting in the advertising boards at the poolside but it also gave me the opportunity to remake some of the func_detail items that looked a little amateur, tables, bannisters, poolside benches etc. I think these models have made a positive difference, giving the map a more professional look. I have also extracted and reskinned source models to help contextualize the map better.

I really hope that people like this version. I am pleased with it and hope very much that players will be able to enjoy good, interesting fights in a fun and imaginative environment. I have tried hard to create a map that is straightforward easy to learn and accessible to new-comers whilst at the same time leaving scope for evolution for players who know the map better - there are a lot of little hiding places, doors,exit signs, lights, cameras... (action?). Bunny-hoppers might be able to get to some fun places on this map, I really dont know. I kinda tried to leave that open a bit. Let me know what you think.

Any feedback more than welcome and if you'd like to use the map on a server, please just send me the IP so I can look in :)

_sText: This is my first map that I have created. Give me feedback, so I can improve the map and make it more fun to play and make it more balanced. I hope you have fun playing this map!

Special thanks to Chizbone for reviewing this map and doing the two nav files for it.

This map is very loosely based on a place called the Old City near where I live. I spent a lot of time ratting around down there last year, drinking beer and looking at old buildings. I also spent some time playing COD 4 and remembering what I love so much about the original COD 1. I tried to incorporate some of that game layout into this map for death match play. I highly recommend mani admin with the random spawn option for this map in cssdm play. Enjoy.

There is a known vertex format error when the map is viewed in spectate or in no clip outside the map boundaries. Basically, the map is too complicated for the engine to render the entire world at once. It seems to have no effect on the server or the player other than spamming the console with the error message.
This is one of my first maps so plz give me good feedback. And... The screenshots are from the first version.... download and youll see 3D Skybox ^^
